aa(lp429
VI was recently caring for a woman in Liberia
p430
aVwho, like my wife, was in her third pregnancy.
p431
aVBut unlike my wife,
p432
aVhad had no prenatal care with her first two babies.
p433
aVShe lived in an isolated community in the forest that had gone for 100 years
p434
aVwithout any health care
p435
aVuntil ...
p436
aVuntil last year when a nurse trained her neighbors
p437
aVto become community health workers.
p438
aa(lp439
VSo here I was,
p440
aVseeing this patient who was in her second trimester,
p441
aVand I pulled out the ultrasound to check on the baby,
p442
aVand she started telling us stories about her first two kids,
p443
aVand I had the ultrasound probe on her belly,
p444
aVand she just stopped mid-sentence.
p445
aVShe turned to me and she said,
p446
aV"Doc, what's that sound?"
p447
aVIt was the first time she'd ever heard her baby's heartbeat.
